	The University of Idaho Alumni Association is proud of your past accomplishments and supportive of your future endeavors.  It is always a resource to have on your side.  No matter where you are, your Alumni Association is there to keep you in touch with your alma mater and friends.
	<p>
	As a member, you enjoy these benefits:
	<ul>
	<li>The University of Idaho Magazine&#151;published quarterly,
	<li>Access to the address records of fellow alumni,
	<li>Regional alumni gatherings and organized class reunions,
	<li>University of Idaho Visa and Long Distance Affinity Cards,
	<li>And many others!
	</ul>
	Your alma mater encourages you to become involved with various programs of the Alumni Asocation:
	<ul>
	<li>Join or organize a local alumni chapter.
	<li>Inform high school students about the University of Idaho.
	<li>Help organize an alumni gathering.
	<li>Help promote the association's scholarship and awards programs.
	<li>Share your ideas, comments and suggests with the Alumni Office.
	<li>Plan a Silver and Gold Day activity for local alumni.
	</ul>
	Take pride in your status as an Idaho alumnus by keeping us informed of your career progress and address changes.  We in turn will let you kow of the latest news about our university, the alumni and upcoming events.</td>
